### `games`
- **Purpose**: A scheduled pickleball session at a club.
- **Android v1**: Required for all discovery, booking, and credit flows.
- **Key columns** (note: baseline DDL predates migrations; inferred from iOS models and Edge Functions):
  - `id UUID PK`
  - `club_id UUID FK → clubs`
  - `recurrence_group_id UUID NULL` — ties together games in a recurring series
  - `title TEXT`
  - `description TEXT NULL`
  - `date_time TIMESTAMPTZ`
  - `duration_minutes INT`
  - `skill_level TEXT` — enum values: `all`, `beginner`, `intermediate`, `advanced` (NOT `tournament`)
  - `game_format TEXT`
  - `game_type TEXT`
  - `max_spots INT`
  - `fee_amount FLOAT8 NULL` — 0 or NULL = free; >0 = paid in dollars (not cents)
  - `fee_currency TEXT NULL` — e.g. `"aud"`
  - `platform_fee_bps INT DEFAULT 1000`
  - `venue_id UUID NULL FK → club_venues`
  - `venue_name TEXT NULL` — legacy fallback
  - `location TEXT NULL`
  - `latitude FLOAT8 NULL` — legacy
  - `longitude FLOAT8 NULL`
  - `status TEXT` — `"active"`, `"cancelled"`
  - `notes TEXT NULL`
  - `requires_dupr BOOL DEFAULT false`
  - `court_count INT DEFAULT 1`
  - `confirmed_count INT NULL` — denormalised; can be stale; prefer live attendee query
  - `waitlist_count INT NULL`
  - `publish_at TIMESTAMPTZ NULL` — NULL = published; future = scheduled/hidden
  - `win_condition TEXT NULL`
  - `created_by UUID NULL`
- **Active game limit trigger**: `check_active_game_limit()` fires BEFORE INSERT. Reads `club_entitlements.max_active_games`. If no entitlement row exists, rejects the insert entirely (deny-by-default). `-1` = unlimited.
- **ANDROID IMPORTANT**: `fee_amount` is stored as FLOAT8 (dollars). PaymentIntent `amount` must be in **cents** (multiply × 100). Android must do the same conversion.

