## 3. RELATIONSHIP MAP

```
auth.users (Supabase managed)
  ↓
  profiles (1:1 — id = auth.uid())
    ↓ avatar_color_key FK
    avatar_palettes (lookup table — fetch once at bootstrap)
  ↓ stripe_customer_id
  club_subscriptions (via clubs.created_by)
  ↓ user_id
  player_credits (UNIQUE per user+club+currency)
  ↓ user_id
  bookings (many per user)
    ↓ game_id
    games (many per club)
      ↓ club_id
      clubs (1:1 created_by → profiles)
        ↓ club_id
        club_entitlements (1:1)
        club_subscriptions (1:1)
        club_stripe_accounts (1:1)
        club_members (1:many)
        club_admins (1:many)
        club_venues (1:many, ONE is_primary)
          ↑ venue_id (on games)
  bookings
    ↓ game_id → games → club_id → player_credits (club-scoped refunds)

app_config (global key/value — fetch at bootstrap)
avatar_palettes (global lookup — fetch at bootstrap)
notifications (1:many per user)
notification_preferences (1:1 per user)
reviews (1:many per game, UNIQUE per game+user)
game_attendance (1:many per game, admin-write)
```

### Fragile Join Areas

1. **`games.venue_id` vs `games.venue_name`**: `venue_id` is canonical FK. `venue_name` is legacy fallback. Use `venue_id → club_venues` for map/address; `venue_name` for display fallback only.

2. **Club address vs `club_venues`**: Same duality at club level. Primary `ClubVenue` (`is_primary = true`) is authoritative for coordinates.

3. **`confirmed_count` on `games`**: Denormalised; can be stale. Use for initial display only; refresh via live attendee query for accuracy.

4. **`profiles → club_admins` join path**: Non-owner admins can only see their own row. Use SECURITY DEFINER RPCs for cross-user admin lookups.

5. **`avatar_color_key` nullable**: NULL means `midnight_navy` default. Never hash user IDs or names to derive a colour — this was the pre-DB design and is explicitly banned.

